# FaIconPickerInput and icon catalogs

## Reuse the shared element

When the renderer needs a **q-icon name** field (template icon, document type icon, future custom fields), use **`FaIconPickerInput`** from **`src/components/elements/FaIconPickerInput/`** with **`v-model`** and a required **`test-locator`**. Do **not** duplicate **`q-menu`** + virtual-scroll icon grids in feature folders.

Playbook: [fantasia-icon-picker skill](../skills/fantasia-icon-picker/SKILL.md).

## Stored value contract

- Persist the **exact q-icon string** Quasar expects on **`q-icon`** / **`q-btn icon=`** (for example **`mdi-file-outline`**, **`fa-solid fa-dragon`**, **`person`**).
- Empty model shows **`FA_ICON_PICKER_EMPTY_PLACEHOLDER_ICON`** (**`mdi-file-outline`**) in the trigger only; emit **`''`** when cleared unless the feature defines otherwise.
- Icon sets available at runtime must stay aligned with **`quasar.config.ts`** **`extras`** and **`FA_ICON_PICKER_PACK_IDS`** in **`types/I_faIconPickerInput.ts`**.

## Catalog pipeline

| Piece | Role |
| --- | --- |
| **`yarn generate:icon-catalogs`** | Regenerate **`src/scripts/faIcons/catalogs/*.catalog.json`** from **`@quasar/extras`** |
| **`faIconPickerCatalogLazyLoadWiring.ts`** | Dynamic **`import()`** of JSON per pack |
| **`faIconPickerMergedCatalogLoadWiring.ts`** | Parallel load + merge for the picker menu |
| **`functions/faIconPickerCatalogFilter.ts`** | Search filter + row chunking for **`QVirtualScroll`** |
| **`types/I_faIconPickerInput.ts`** | Pack ids, **`FA_ICON_PICKER_ICONS_PER_ROW`**, **`FA_ICON_PICKER_VIRTUAL_ROW_HEIGHT_PX`** |

After **`@quasar/extras`** upgrades or icon-set changes, run **`yarn generate:icon-catalogs`** and commit catalog JSON — do not hand-maintain large lists.

## Layout constants (TS ↔ SCSS)

**`FA_ICON_PICKER_ICONS_PER_ROW`** (16) and **`FA_ICON_PICKER_VIRTUAL_ROW_HEIGHT_PX`** (52) must match **`styles/_variables.scss`** (**`$faIconPickerInput-iconsPerRow`**, **`$faIconPickerInput-virtualRow-height`**) and **`FaIconPickerInputMenuPanel`** **`:virtual-scroll-item-size`**.

## Menu grid styling

- List cells use **flat** **`q-btn`** (**`dense`**, **`flat`**) — **not** **`round`** — so wide glyphs are not clipped.
- Set **`overflow: visible`** on row/cell rules when adjusting layout; keep **`place-items: center`** on the icon grid row.

## i18n and Storybook

- Strings live under **`i18n/<locale>/components/elements/FaIconPickerInput/`**, keyed **`faIconPickerInput`** in **`index.ts`**.
- Add matching imports to **`.storybook-workspace/.storybook/mocks/externalFileLoader.ts`** when extending copy.

## Two-level architecture

- **`src/scripts/faIcons/functions/`** — level-1 pure helpers only.
- **`faIconPickerInput_manager.ts`** — wiring-only manager for **`useFaIconPickerInput`**.
- Feature composable factory: **`faIconPickerInputComposableWiring.ts`** (not under **`functions/`**).

## Tests

- Extend **`FaIconPickerInput`** Vitest and **`src/scripts/faIcons`** **`_tests/`** when changing catalog or menu behavior.
- User flows: Playwright via **`data-test-locator`**, **`data-test-icon-name`**, menu search + cell click (see **`DialogProjectSettings.playwright.test.ts`**).

## TypeScript interfaces and types (`types/`)

- Put shared `interface` / `type` declarations in repository-root `types/` (import with `app/types/...`). Prefer one domain-oriented module per feature area with brief JSDoc on exports (see `types/I_appMenusDataList.ts`). Do not add colocated `<filename>.types.ts` under `src/`, `src-electron/`, or `.storybook-workspace/`. Ambient augmentations for third-party modules also live under `types/` and are loaded with a side-effect import from the owning boot file or `src/stores/index.ts` (see `types/piniaModuleAugmentation.ts`).
- For JavaScript (`.js`), TypeScript (`.ts`), Vue (`.vue`), and JSON (`.json`, `.jsonc`, `.json5`) files, enforce expanded multi-line object literals via ESLint (`object-curly-newline` + `object-property-newline`) and keep files auto-fixable with `eslint --fix`.
